# Token Efficiency Rules

## Before reading files
- Read only files directly relevant to the task
- Never read entire directories speculatively
- Use grep/search instead of opening files to verify content exists first
- Never re-read a file already read in the same session

## Before writing code
- Modify only the minimal set of files required
- Do not refactor code unrelated to the task
- Do not add comments unless asked
- Do not add docstrings unless asked
- Do not create example/test files unless asked

## Responses
- No preamble ("Sure!", "Great question", "Of course")
- No summary of what you just did — the diff speaks for itself
- No "Next steps" unless asked
- No explanation of unchanged code
- Errors only: skip warnings that don't affect the task

## Tool calls
- Prefer targeted grep over full file reads
- Never call the same tool twice for the same data
- Batch related edits into one tool call where possible

## Scope
- Do exactly what was asked — nothing more
- Do not proactively fix unrelated issues
- Do not upgrade dependencies unless the task requires it
- Do not add imports beyond what the task needs
